Nexus Project: Complete Developer Guide

This document is a comprehensive, production-ready blueprint for the Nexus Project. It guides a developer or agent through the entire process of setting up a highly scalable and secure local environment, building a microservice, and preparing it for automated deployment to a production environment.

1. Context and Project Overview

The Nexus Project is a foundational container infrastructure platform leveraging Docker and Kubernetes to establish a standardized, secure, and scalable environment for future containerized applications. This platform aims to accelerate the time-to-market for new services by providing a pre-built infrastructure that handles core concerns like consistency, efficient deployment, and secure communication1. This guide details a complete, production-grade workflow that includes advanced scalability, security, and automation practices, moving beyond the initial "platform skeleton" to a fully functional system2222.


